SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION MAKES ITS GOVERNING DOCUMENTS, CONFLICT OF INTEREST
POLICY AND FORM 990 AVAILABLE UPON WRITTEN REQUEST.
THE CEO AND CFO OVERSEE FINANCIAL STATEMENT PREPARATION AND AUDIT ENGAGEMENT.
THE CEO, CFO AND FINANCE COMMITTEE REVIEW THE FORM 990.
ANNUALLY THE CONFLICT OF INTEREST STATEMENT IS SIGNED BY BOARD MEMBERS AND
REVIEWED BY THE ENTIRE BOARD. BOARD MEMBERS SHALL EXCUSE THEMSELVES FROM
ISSUES THAT ENHANCE THE PROBABILITY OF THEIR OWN PERSONAL AND PRIVATE GAIN.
STATE AND NATIONAL SALARY COMPARISONS ARE USED TO ESTABLISH SALARY LIMITS
FOR TOP MANAGEMENT OFFICIALS. PERFORMANCE EVALUATIONS ARE PREFORMED ANNUALLY
AND SALARY INCREASES ARE BOARD APPROVED.
